$ VBA: longLong only in 64-bit environments

The data type → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/longLong[`longLong`] is only defined in 64 bit (→ Microsoft/Office) environments. Thus, before declaring it, we want to be sure we're actually running
in such an environment and check it with the → development/languages/VBA/compiler-directives/conditional-compilation[`#if … then`] compiler construct.

gh|about-VBA|/compiler-directives/winX/longLong.bas||

sa:
  → development/languages/VBA/compiler-directives[Compiler directives]
